{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9da6b455c7570a3a","input":{"filename":"hr_onboarding_prioritized_action_report.md","title":"HR Onboarding Assistant Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# HR Onboarding Assistant – Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Generated on:** 2026-06-18\n\n## Evidence Base\n- Dossier loaded for agent **28‑hr‑onboarding‑assistant** (HR onboarding assistant, People Ops). \n- Records analyzed (limit = 10) yielded three relevant items (totalRecords = 3) with combined risk = 16 and opportunity = 10.6.\n  - **Record 28‑A** – *Urgent priority case* (impact = 50,876, risk = 5, score = {risk 9, opportunity 7}).\n  - **Record 28‑C** – *Blocked follow‑up* (impact = 23,908, risk = 3, score = {risk 5, opportunity 2.4}).\n  - **Record 28‑B** – *Routine queue item* (impact = 12,164, risk = 2, score = {risk 2, opportunity 1.2}).\n\n**Assumptions**\n1. Impact numbers approximate business value of completing the item.\n2. “Urgent” status implies the item should be tackled first, regardless of risk score.\n3. “Blocked” status indicates a dependency that must be resolved before any downstream work can proceed.\n4. No additional hidden records exist beyond the three returned by `analyze_records`.\n\n## Prioritization Logic\n| Rank | Record | Status | Impact | Risk Score | Rationale |\n|------|--------|--------|--------|------------|-----------|\n| 1 | **28‑A** – Priority case | urgent | 50,876 | 9 (high) | Highest impact and already flagged urgent; addressing this will deliver the greatest immediate value and reduce the highest risk score. |\n| 2 | **28‑C** – Blocked follow‑up | blocked | 23,908 | 5 (moderate) | Substantial impact but progress halted by a cross‑functional dependency. Clearing the blockage unlocks further work and prevents downstream delays. |\n| 3 | **28‑B** – Routine queue item | in_review | 12,164 | 2 (low) | Lower impact and risk; suitable for standard processing after the above items are cleared. |\n\n## Recommended Action Plan (≤ 500 words)\n### 1. Immediate Execution – Record 28‑A (Urgent Priority Case)\n- **Task:** Draft and publish a standardized onboarding plan template for new hires.\n- **Sub‑tasks:**\n  1. Gather existing onboarding artifacts from People Ops.\n  2. Define mandatory checklist items (e.g., equipment provisioning, account creation, compliance training).\n  3. Implement a tracking dashboard (e.g., in the internal HR portal) to surface missing setup tasks.\n- **Owner:** People Ops – HR Onboarding Lead.\n- **Deadline:** 48 hours.\n- **Success Metric:** 100 % of new hires in the next cohort have a completed onboarding checklist within their first week.\n\n### 2. Dependency Resolution – Record 28‑C (Blocked Follow‑up)\n- **Task:** Identify and clear the cross‑functional block.\n- **Steps:**\n  1. Contact the referenced external team (e.g., IT Security) to confirm required approvals.\n  2. Document the dependency in the shared project tracker.\n  3. Schedule a short sync (≤ 30 min) to obtain sign‑off.\n- **Owner:** People Ops – Onboarding Coordinator (with support from IT liaison).\n- **Deadline:** 5 business days.\n- **Success Metric:** Dependency cleared and work on Record 28‑C resumed.\n\n### 3. Routine Processing – Record 28‑B (Routine Queue Item)\n- **Task:** Review the routine queue item for potential automation.\n- **Actions:**\n  1. Verify the current status and any pending approvals.\n  2. Evaluate if the item can be batched with other low‑risk tasks.\n  3. Close the item or move it to “completed” after verification.\n- **Owner:** People Ops – HR Operations Analyst.\n- **Deadline:** 10 business days.\n- **Success Metric:** Item resolved without escalations.\n\n## Next Steps & Monitoring\n1. **Publish the report** to the HR Ops drive and notify the onboarding lead.\n2. **Track progress** via the HR Ops dashboard; update status daily for the first week.\n3. **Re‑run `analyze_records`** after two weeks to capture any new high‑impact items and adjust priorities accordingly.\n\n---\n*Report generated automatically by the HR Onboarding Assistant (Agent 28‑hr‑onboarding‑assistant) following the operating playbook.*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:18:24.229Z"}}
